✅ Simple English Explanation

JWT (JSON Web Token) is a secure way to transmit information between client and server in the form of a token.

It is mainly used for authentication and authorization.

When a user logs in:

The server verifies username and password.

If correct, the server generates a JWT token.

That token is sent back to the client.

The client stores it (usually in localStorage or cookies).

For every protected request, the client sends that token in the header.

The server verifies the token and allows access.

So instead of checking username/password every time, the server just checks the token.

👉 Short interview line:
"JWT is a stateless authentication mechanism where the server generates a signed token after login, and the client uses that token to access protected APIs."



✅ Simple Hinglish Explanation

JWT ek secure token system hai jo login ke baad user ko diya jata hai.

Step-by-step samjho:

User login karta hai email/password se.

Server check karta hai credentials sahi hai ya nahi.

Agar sahi hai, toh server ek JWT token generate karta hai.

Ye token client ko milta hai.

Jab bhi user koi protected API hit karta hai, toh wo token header me bhejta hai.

Server token verify karta hai — agar valid hai toh access milta hai.

Iska main benefit:
Server ko har baar database me password check nahi karna padta.
Token verify karke hi pata chal jata hai user authorized hai ya nahi.

👉 Interview me bol sakte ho:
"JWT is used for secure and stateless authentication. After successful login, the server generates a signed token which is sent with every request to access protected resources."


JWT Structure (Thoda Technical)

JWT 3 parts me hota hai:

Header

Payload

Signature

Format hota hai:
xxxxx.yyyyy.zzzzz

Header → Algorithm batata hai (like HS256)

Payload → User data (like user_id, role)

Signature → Security ke liye hoti hai (tampering prevent karta hai)

🔥 Why JWT is Preferred?

Stateless (server session store nahi karta)

Scalable for microservices

Secure (digitally signed)

Fast verification

🎯 Real Example (E-commerce)

Login → JWT mil gaya
User order place kare → token verify
Admin panel access → token me role check

